📌 What is Auto Scaling Group (ASG)?
        ASG (Auto Scaling Group) is an AWS service that automatically launches or terminates EC2 instances based on demand 
      — ensuring your application always has the right number of instances running at the right time.

🖥️ Part 1 — Create Launch Template:
        Step 1 — Navigate:
                Go to AWS Console → EC2
                In the left panel → Click "Launch Templates"
                Click "Create Launch Template"
        Step 2 — Configure Launch Template:
                Setting	                Value
                Launch Template Name	demo-lt
                Description	        Launch Template for ASG Demo
                OS / AMI	        Amazon Linux 2
                Instance Type	        t2.micro(Free Tier)
                Key Pair	        EC2 Tutorial1
                Security Group	        launch-wizard-1
                ⚠️ Correction: You wrote demo-tg as the launch template name — but demo-tg is already used for the Target Group. Use demo-lt to avoid confusion.
        Step 3 — Add User Data (Bootstrap Script):
                Expand "Advanced Details"
                Scroll down to "User Data"
                Paste the following: from Bootstraping page   
                Click "Create Launch Template" ✅
====================================================================================================================
⚖️ Part 2 — Create Auto Scaling Group:
        Step 1 — Navigate:
                Go to AWS Console → EC2
                In the left panel → Scroll down → Click "Auto Scaling Groups"
                Click "Create Auto Scaling Group"
        Step 2 — Name & Launch Template:
                Setting	                        Value
                Auto Scaling Group Name	        Demo-ASG
                Launch Template	Click Refresh → Select demo-lt
                Click "Next" ✅
        Step 3 — Network / Availability Zones:
                Under Network → Select your VPC(Default VPC)
                Under Availability Zones and Subnets → Select ALL available AZs
        
                AZ	        Action
                ap-south-1a	✅ Select
                ap-south-1b	✅ Select
                ap-south-1c	✅ Select
                Click "Next" ✅
        Step 4 — Attach to Existing Load Balancer:
                Select "Attach to an existing load balancer"
                Select "Choose from your load balancer target groups"
                Select demo-tg-alb from the dropdown ✅
                            Setting	        Value
                        Load Balancing	        Attach to existing load balancer
                        Target Group	        demo-tg-alb
                        Health Check Type	EC2 (leave as default)
                        Click "Next" ✅
        Step 5 — Configure Group Size:
                        Setting	                Value
                        Desired Capacity	1
                        Minimum Capacity	1
                        Maximum Capacity	3
                💡 Start with Desired: 1 — we will scale up to 2 manually after creation to verify everything works.
                Leave all other settings as default
                Click "Next" → "Next" → "Next" → "Create Auto Scaling Group" ✅
================================================================================================================
✅ Part 3 — Verify ASG Created Instance:
        Step 1 — Check Activity Tab:
                Go to EC2 → Auto Scaling Groups
                Select Demo-ASG
                Click "Activity" tab
                You will see a log entry:
                Status: Successful ✅
                Description: Launching a new EC2 instance: i-0xxxxxxxxxx
                Start Time: [timestamp]
                💡 ASG has automatically launched 1 EC2 instance based on Desired Capacity = 1
        Step 2 — Verify Target Group Health:
                Go to EC2 → Target Groups
                Select demo-tg-alb
                Click "Targets" tab
                The ASG-launched instance should show:
                Instance	Health Status
                i-0xxxxxxxxxx (ASG instance)	✅ Healthy
        Step 3 — Test via ALB DNS:
                Go to EC2 → Load Balancers
                Select ELB-Demo-ALB
                Copy the DNS Name
                Open browser → Paste DNS URL:
                http://ELB-Demo-ALB-xxxx.ap-south-1.elb.amazonaws.com
                Result:
                Hello World from ip-172-31-x-x.ap-south-1.compute.internal ✅
================================================================================================================
📈 Part 4 — Scale Up to 2 Instances:
        Step 1 — Edit Desired Capacity:
                Go to EC2 → Auto Scaling Groups
                Select Demo-ASG
                Click "Edit"(top right of Overview section)
                Update:
        
                Setting	Old Value	New Value
                Desired Capacity	1	2
                Minimum Capacity	1	1
                Maximum Capacity	3	3
                Click "Update" ✅
                ⏳ ASG will automatically launch a second EC2 instance within 1–2 minutes.
        Step 2 — Verify Both Instances Healthy:
                Go to EC2 → Target Groups
                Select demo-tg-alb → "Targets" tab
                Both instances should show:
                Instance	Health Status
                i-0xxxxxxxxxx (Instance 1)	✅ Healthy
                i-0yyyyyyyyyy (Instance 2)	✅ Healthy
        Step 3 — Test Load Balancing:
                Open browser → Paste ALB DNS URL
                Refresh multiple times:
                Refresh 1 → Hello World from ip-172-31-x-x (Instance 1) ✅
                Refresh 2 → Hello World from ip-172-31-y-y (Instance 2) ✅
                Refresh 3 → Hello World from ip-172-31-x-x (Instance 1) ✅
                (Round Robin — both instances serving traffic) ✅
==============================================================================================
🔑 Key Rules to Remember:
ASG = Auto Scaling Group
    = Automatically manages EC2 instance count

Key Settings:
├── Desired Capacity → How many instances RIGHT NOW
├── Minimum Capacity → NEVER go below this count
├── Maximum Capacity → NEVER go above this count
└── Launch Template  → HOW to launch each new instance

ASG + ALB + Target Group:
ASG launches EC2 → Auto registers in demo-tg-alb
ALB distributes traffic → Across all healthy instances
Health check fails → ASG terminates & replaces instance ✅

Path:
EC2 → Auto Scaling Groups → Demo-ASG
→ Activity tab → verify instance launched
→ Target Groups → demo-tg-alb → Healthy ✅
→ ALB DNS → Traffic works across all instances ✅
